    "codebase_summary": "The codebase is designed for analyzing various types of documents and code repositories, providing functionality for file format support display, Git repository analysis, and contributor metrics. The main program, as indicated in `list_supported_formats.py`, showcases a comprehensive list of supported file formats across different categories such as documents, presentations, spreadsheets, code files, and markup/data formats. This feature is aimed at users who need to understand the types of files the program can handle.\n\nKey technologies utilized in this project include Python, along with various libraries for handling document parsing and Git operations. The architecture comprises different modules like `GitAnalyzer`, `ContributorAnalyzer`, and `CodeQualityAnalyzer`, which encapsulate specific functionalities related to Git repository analysis, contributor statistics, and code quality assessments. The code structure is modular, allowing for easy extension and maintenance, with each analyzer class dedicated to a particular aspect of the analysis process.",
